<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="828" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d828">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7370/32.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Norwegian Chargé</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Norwegian Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">White
                                        Sulphur Springs, W. Va.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-01"><hi rend="italic">July 1,
                                        1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>It is my sad duty to announce the death of Honorable O. Gude, minister
                            for Norway, to-night at 10 o’clock.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morgenstierne.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>